thread.title: U.S. Government Bond Yields Flatline Following Fair Two-Year Auction

author: Akane Otani
title: U.S. Government Bond Yields Flatline Following Fair Two-Year Auction
text:
U.S. government bonds stalled Tuesday as a dearth of economic data and a relatively uneventful debt auction left many investors sitting on the sidelines.
The yield on the benchmark 10-year U.S. Treasury note settled at 3.065%, unchanged from Monday.
